name: politico
text: Trump dropped his final federal lawsuit in Michigan yesterday, but he continues to baselessly claim that he won the election. @TimAlberta explains how this may become a story Republicans continue to tell even after Trump leaves the White House in January. https://t.co/3XJNenzd7r https://t.co/rRbOzi9JvE

name: politico
text: Gavin Newsom has dissolved California's economic task force, despite rising Covid-19 case numbers. The group concluded its work with a report outlining general principles and findings—but no new initiatives to protect California businesses in the pandemic. https://t.co/sKaBxKu99m

text:
Gathering students and teachers under the same roof isn’t foolproof.  

But research shows that's not what's triggering the surge of cases across the nation or around the world.  https://t.co/1HMB2FMKpO

text:
13 of the first 14 White House appointments are going to former Biden staffers— some from the 2020 campaign, but also many who go back decades. The hires are part of a larger dynamic in Biden-world: he values loyalty.
